{@--1@} To sit near to (with
<ab>acc.</ab>), sit at the side of (as a mark of
submission and respect); wait upon,
serve, worship;  
{#udyAnapAlasAmAnyamftavastamupAsate#} <ls>Ku. 2. 36</ls>;  
{#aMbAmupAssva sadayAM#} <ls>Aśvad. 13</ls>; <ls>Śi. 16. 47</ls>;
<ls>Ms. 3. 189.</ls>

{@--4@} To approach, go to or
towards; {#upAsAMcakrire drazwuM#} 
{#devagaMDarvakinnarAH#} <ls>Bk. 5. 107</ls>; {#paralokamupAsmahe#}  
<ls n="Bk.">7. 89.</ls>

{@--6@} To be 
intent upon, be engaged in, take part
in, (perform as a sacred rite);
{#upAsya paScimAM saMDyAM#} <ls>K. 176</ls>, <ls n="K.">179</ls>;
{#tepyupAsaMtu me maKaM#} <ls>Mb.</ls>; <ls>Ms. 2. 222</ls>,  
<ls n="Ms.">3. 104</ls>, <ls n="Ms.">7. 223</ls>, <ls n="Ms.">11. 42.</ls>

{@--7@} To 
undergo, suffer; {#alaM te pAMquputrARAM BaktyA#}
{#klaMSamupAsituM#} <ls>Mb.</ls>; <ls>Ms. 11. 184.</ls>

{@--8@}
To remain or continue in any state
or action; <ab>oft.</ab> with a {%<ab>pres. p.</ab>%};  
<ls>Bg. 12. 6.</ls>

{@--11@}
To resort to, employ, apply, use;
{#lakzaRopAsyate yasya kfte#} <ls>S. D. 2</ls>;
{#vastirupAsyamAnaH#} <ls>Suśr.</ls>
